reviews.text: Very good Chinese restaurant, not too oily, like home made dishes.  Got some signature rice in a pot which needs at least 4 people to finish.  Not too crowded on weekends, which is a good choice for family dinner.
Good food, good service. Small dishes. Price is a bit higher than you expect. Anyway worth a trial
Special dishes not always made in market.  taste good.

Humm, mixed feelings about this place. The food is good and slightly creative. Cantonese food when done well is so fabulous that one should not mess with the classics. Yet they have done a twist or two. 
A dish of shredded chicken with sesame oil dressing takes on a new form, with shredded chicken thigh meat and shredded goose thigh meat. Fantastic combo that works so well we ordered seconds.
Pan fried cuttlefish patties are given a new refreshing twist by adding watercress to the mix and fried to brown perfection. Really good.
But the crab, in a casserole with Cantonese steamed vermicelli rolls to absorb the crab coral, was just OK but it is by far the most expensive of the dishes we ordered.
So I suppose, come here for slightely inventive but well executed dishes and stay away from the big ticket items.
Good food

Very good Chinese restaurant, not too oily, like home made dishes.  Got some signature rice in a pot which needs at least 4 people to finish.  Not too crowded on weekends, which is a good choice for family dinner.
第一次食蜑家菜，全部餸都太咸！椒鹽鮮魷&蜜餞蝦球個炸漿厚身唔夠脆，而且魷魚唔新鮮😰水佬砂鍋蜆直頭咸到食唔到！咁嘅質素食物全部都over price👎🏻服務又差！
正，地方同菜式都好味，招牌菜，手撕雞鴨係加餸必選

以蜑家菜作核心 海鮮是必然 薑粒蒸咸鮮魚
煎墨魚餅 銀魚乾 蝦乾煲仔飯⋯
這裡椅子較緊迫
